reviews.text:
I came in early to this dental clinic, being the first patient. Unlike other clinics where the first patient is usually seen promptly to reduce waiting time for others, this clinic took a different approach. They spoke to me politely and explained that they needed to complete their cleaning and sanitation routine before attending to any patients.

This extra time is critical, especially for a dental clinic, where hygiene directly impacts patient safety and care standards. It showed their commitment to maintaining a sterile environment and following proper protocols. Rather than rushing, they prioritized cleanliness and professionalism. It gave me confidence in their practices.

What surprised me even more was seeing the lady at the reception helping with the cleaning. She didn‚Äôt just sit behind the desk ‚Äî she actively contributed to preparing the clinic. It showed teamwork and a shared sense of responsibility. That level of dedication was both rare and impressive. It made a strong first impression.

Next, the dental doctor ‚Äî truly, no words can describe the experience. Calm and patient, the doctor took the time to explain every step in detail. Even though I was slow to understand at times, there was no rush or frustration. Instead, the doctor ensured I was comfortable and fully aware of what was happening.

It‚Äôs rare to come across a professional so dedicated to communication and patient care. The clarity and reassurance I received made a huge difference. I felt respected and valued as a patient. What could have been an anxious visit turned into a calm and educational experience. This kind of approach builds trust instantly. What an experience ‚Äî truly outstanding.

reviews.name: Alex Low
reviews.text: Had my root canal treatment done here. Dr. Neoh was incredibly knowledgeable in handling the procedure. It‚Äôs been five years since the treatment, and my dental health has been very consistent since switching to Dr. Neoh as my go-to dentist. Definite recommend!

reviews.name: Narendranath Ramana
reviews.text:
I visited 32T Dental for what was supposed to be a simple molar tooth surgery.
Removing a molar is never easy‚Äîit demands skill, patience, and a deep sense of care. Yet, from the moment I stepped in, everything felt surprisingly calm, almost as if I was exactly where I was meant to be.

By a stroke of luck, I found myself under the care of Dr. Neoh Ein Yau.
A wonderful soul‚Äîcalm, gentle, and deeply professional. His soft voice, steady hands, and reassuring smile washed away every ounce of fear. He didn‚Äôt just treat a tooth; he treated a human being‚Äîwith dignity, patience, and heart. For that, I am profoundly grateful.

Thanks to the sophisticated equipment and Dr. Neoh‚Äôs vast experience, the procedure unfolded with incredible smoothness and comfort.
There was no struggle, no discomfort‚Äîonly a quiet confidence in the air, like a symphony played by a master. In that peaceful half-hour, my mind drifted elsewhere.

As I lay silently in the chair, memories of my late mother rose within me like a soft, unspoken prayer.
‚ÄúNaren, please brush your teeth before you sleep,‚Äù she would say with a smile, night after night.
‚ÄúDon‚Äôt eat sweets‚Äîthey will spoil your teeth,‚Äù she would remind me, her voice filled with a tenderness only a mother can give.
Those simple words, once brushed aside by my youthful stubbornness, now echoed louder than ever in my heart. In that moment, her love wrapped around me like an invisible blanket.

A mother‚Äôs love never dies.
It lingers quietly‚Äîin our small habits, in fleeting thoughts, in the spaces between heartbeats. She gave so much, asked for so little, and loved without conditions. Years later, her gentle spirit still walks beside me, unseen but deeply felt‚Äîlike a hand resting lightly on my shoulder.
What once felt like mere reminders now feel like sacred truths.
In that quiet chair, I realized: love like hers never leaves you. It becomes part of who you are.

So often we think we know better‚Äîwe ignore their words, thinking we‚Äôll figure it out ourselves.
But life has a way of circling back, teaching us with gentleness and sometimes with tears, that mothers always knew best.

Returning to the present, I couldn‚Äôt help but notice how special 32T Dental was.
Every staff member, from the front desk to the nurses, carried themselves with such grace and warmth.
They didn‚Äôt just provide a service‚Äîthey gave comfort, kindness, and care, in a world that often forgets how badly we all need them.

Dr. Neoh Ein Yau, though perhaps 15 years my junior, treated me with a reverence usually reserved for someone‚Äôs father.
His voice was soft, his words full of respect. His kindness was never hurried, never mechanical‚Äîit was sincere and effortless.
He explained every step with the patience of someone who truly understood human fears.
There was a quiet dignity in the way he worked, a rare and beautiful thing in today‚Äôs fast-paced world.
In that moment, age, titles, roles‚Äînone of it mattered. What mattered was the connection between two human beings, built on respect and compassion.

It is extraordinary how a simple dental visit turned into a profound life moment.
Not pain, but peace.
Not fear, but reflection.
Not discomfort, but overwhelming gratitude.

To Dr. Neoh, his wonderful team at 32T Dental, and above all, to the enduring, everlasting love of my late mother‚Äî
Thank you. Thank you from the depths of a heart that will never forget.

reviews.text:
Sharing on behalf of my friend's review:
Overall, I found my experience at Lumiere Clinic to be a waste of my time and energy. While I appreciated the friendliness and professionalism of the front desk staff, the consultation itself was disappointing. The doctor appeared indecisive and did not offer any clear professional advice or direction. Instead of guiding me with confidence, he listed out several vague treatment options without recommending one based on medical reasoning or expertise, even when I specifically asked for his opinion.

What was more frustrating was that the diagnosis I received turned out to be incorrect. I was told the issue was with my tooth and that extraction should be considered. However, I later visited another clinic for a second opinion, where the dentist quickly identified the actual cause of the discomfort, a minor gum issue due to something being lodged in the gum area. The issue was resolved without any invasive procedures, and there was no need to remove the tooth at all.

It felt as though the doctor‚Äôs default response was to suggest extraction rather than thoroughly diagnosing the root cause of my symptoms. This approach gave me little confidence in the clinic‚Äôs ability to provide accurate, solution-based care. For patients who already know exactly what they want done, Lumiere might be sufficient. But for anyone looking for professional advice or proper diagnosis, I would strongly recommend seeking a more experienced opinion elsewhere.

This experience left me frustrated and disappointed. I hope the clinic takes this feedback seriously and works to improve its diagnostic process and communication between doctors and patients.

TLDR:  a waste of my time and energy
